You are an expert in Chrome Extension Manifest V3, JavaScript/TypeScript, Web APIs, Chrome Extension APIs, and browser security.

# Project Type
This is a Chrome Extension built with Manifest V3 (MV3), using TypeScript, and following Google's latest extension development guidelines.

## Tech Stack
- Manifest V3
- TypeScript or modern JavaScript (ES2022+)
- Chrome Extension APIs
- Service Worker (background)
- Web APIs (DOM, Fetch, Storage)
- Vite or webpack for bundling

## Manifest V3 Key Changes from MV2

- Background pages replaced with **Service Workers** (no persistent state)
- `chrome.scripting.executeScript()` replaces `chrome.tabs.executeScript()`
- `chrome.action` replaces `chrome.browserAction` / `chrome.pageAction`
- Host permissions must be declared separately from optional permissions
- Remote code execution is PROHIBITED
- Use `declarativeNetRequest` instead of `webRequest` for blocking

## Project Structure

```
extension/
  manifest.json
  src/
    background/
      service-worker.ts      # Background service worker
      message-handler.ts
    content/
      content-script.ts      # Injected into web pages
      injected.ts            # Injected into page context
    popup/
      popup.html
      popup.ts
    options/
      options.html
      options.ts
    sidepanel/               # If using side panel
      sidepanel.html
      sidepanel.ts
    utils/
      storage.ts
      messaging.ts
      api.ts
    types/
      chrome.d.ts            # Custom Chrome type extensions
      messages.ts            # Message type definitions
  icons/
    icon16.png
    icon48.png
    icon128.png
  dist/                      # Built output
```

## manifest.json Structure

```json
{
  "manifest_version": 3,
  "name": "My Extension",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Extension description",
  "permissions": [
    "storage",
    "tabs",
    "activeTab"
  ],
  "host_permissions": [
    "https://api.example.com/*"
  ],
  "optional_permissions": [
    "notifications"
  ],
  "background": {
    "service_worker": "dist/background/service-worker.js",
    "type": "module"
  },
  "content_scripts": [
    {
      "matches": ["<all_urls>"],
      "js": ["dist/content/content-script.js"],
      "run_at": "document_idle"
    }
  ],
  "action": {
    "default_popup": "popup.html",
    "default_icon": {
      "16": "icons/icon16.png",
      "48": "icons/icon48.png",
      "128": "icons/icon128.png"
    }
  },
  "options_ui": {
    "page": "options.html",
    "open_in_tab": true
  },
  "side_panel": {
    "default_path": "sidepanel.html"
  }
}
```

## Service Worker (Background) Patterns

```typescript
// background/service-worker.ts
// 注意：Service Worker 无法访问 DOM，也无持久状态
// 不要在顶层保存状态 — 使用 chrome.storage

chrome.runtime.onInstalled.addListener((details) => {
  if (details.reason === 'install') {
    // 初始化默认设置
    chrome.storage.sync.set({ theme: 'light', enabled: true });
    console.log('[Background] 扩展安装完成');
  }
});

// 监听来自 popup/content script 的消息
chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener((message, sender, sendResponse) => {
  // 必须返回 true 才能使用异步 sendResponse
  handleMessage(message, sender)
    .then(sendResponse)
    .catch((error) => {
      console.error('[Background] 消息处理失败:', error);
      sendResponse({ error: error.message });
    });
  return true; // 保持消息通道开放
});

async function handleMessage(message: ExtensionMessage, sender: chrome.runtime.MessageSender) {
  switch (message.type) {
    case 'FETCH_DATA':
      return await fetchData(message.payload);
    case 'GET_SETTINGS':
      return await getSettings();
    default:
      throw new Error(`未知消息类型: ${message.type}`);
  }
}
```

## Messaging System

```typescript
// types/messages.ts — 类型安全的消息系统
export type ExtensionMessage =
  | { type: 'FETCH_DATA'; payload: { url: string } }
  | { type: 'GET_SETTINGS' }
  | { type: 'UPDATE_SETTING'; payload: { key: string; value: unknown } }
  | { type: 'CONTENT_READY' };

export type ExtensionResponse<T = unknown> =
  | { success: true; data: T }
  | { success: false; error: string };

// utils/messaging.ts
export async function sendToBackground<T>(
  message: ExtensionMessage
): Promise<ExtensionResponse<T>> {
  return chrome.runtime.sendMessage(message);
}

export async function sendToTab<T>(
  tabId: number,
  message: ExtensionMessage
): Promise<ExtensionResponse<T>> {
  return chrome.tabs.sendMessage(tabId, message);
}
```

## Storage Utilities

```typescript
// utils/storage.ts
interface ExtensionSettings {
  theme: 'light' | 'dark';
  enabled: boolean;
  apiKey?: string;
}

export const storage = {
  async get<K extends keyof ExtensionSettings>(
    key: K
  ): Promise<ExtensionSettings[K] | undefined> {
    const result = await chrome.storage.sync.get(key);
    return result[key];
  },

  async set<K extends keyof ExtensionSettings>(
    key: K,
    value: ExtensionSettings[K]
  ): Promise<void> {
    await chrome.storage.sync.set({ [key]: value });
  },

  async getAll(): Promise<Partial<ExtensionSettings>> {
    return chrome.storage.sync.get(null);
  },

  onChange(
    callback: (changes: Partial<Record<keyof ExtensionSettings, chrome.storage.StorageChange>>) => void
  ) {
    chrome.storage.onChanged.addListener((changes, area) => {
      if (area === 'sync') callback(changes as any);
    });
  },
};
```

## Content Script Patterns

```typescript
// content/content-script.ts
// 在网页上下文中运行，可以访问 DOM

(function() {
  'use strict';

  // 防止多次注入
  if (window.__extensionInjected) return;
  window.__extensionInjected = true;

  // 监听来自 background 的消息
  chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener((message, sender, sendResponse) => {
    if (message.type === 'GET_PAGE_INFO') {
      sendResponse({
        success: true,
        data: {
          title: document.title,
          url: window.location.href,
          selectedText: window.getSelection()?.toString() ?? '',
        },
      });
    }
    return true;
  });

  // 向 background 发送消息
  async function reportPageLoad() {
    await chrome.runtime.sendMessage({
      type: 'CONTENT_READY',
    });
  }

  if (document.readyState === 'loading') {
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', reportPageLoad);
  } else {
    reportPageLoad();
  }
})();
```

## Popup Patterns

```typescript
// popup/popup.ts
import { storage } from '../utils/storage';
import { sendToBackground } from '../utils/messaging';

document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', async () => {
  const settings = await storage.getAll();
  initUI(settings);

  document.getElementById('toggle')?.addEventListener('click', async () => {
    const enabled = !(await storage.get('enabled'));
    await storage.set('enabled', enabled);
    updateToggleUI(enabled);
  });
});

async function getCurrentTab(): Promise<chrome.tabs.Tab | undefined> {
  const [tab] = await chrome.tabs.query({ active: true, currentWindow: true });
  return tab;
}
```

## Error Handling Patterns

```typescript
// 包装 Chrome API 调用
async function safeChromeTabs(tabId: number) {
  try {
    return await chrome.tabs.get(tabId);
  } catch (error) {
    // Tab 可能已关闭
    if ((error as Error).message?.includes('No tab with id')) {
      return null;
    }
    throw error;
  }
}

// 检查扩展上下文是否仍有效（防止 Extension context invalidated 错误）
function isExtensionContextValid(): boolean {
  try {
    chrome.runtime.getURL('');
    return true;
  } catch {
    return false;
  }
}
```

## Security Best Practices

- NEVER use `eval()` or `new Function()` — MV3 禁止
- NEVER inject remote scripts
- Sanitize all DOM insertions to prevent XSS
- Use `chrome.storage` not `localStorage` for extension data
- Validate all messages from content scripts (they can be compromised)
- Use Content Security Policy in manifest
- Request minimal permissions — principle of least privilege

## File Naming Conventions

- Manifest: `manifest.json` (root)
- Service worker: `service-worker.ts`
- Content scripts: `content-script.ts`
- Message types: `messages.ts`
- Utils: `camelCase.ts`

## What Cursor Should Do

- Use `chrome.storage.sync` for settings, `chrome.storage.local` for large data
- Return `true` from `onMessage` listener for async responses
- Generate typed message interfaces to avoid runtime errors
- Suggest `chrome.scripting.executeScript()` (MV3) not `chrome.tabs.executeScript()`
- Check `chrome.runtime.lastError` after Chrome API calls
- Suggest minimal permission sets

## What Cursor Should Avoid

- Do NOT use `background.persistent: true` (MV2 pattern)
- Do NOT use `chrome.browserAction` (use `chrome.action`)
- Do NOT use `eval()` or dynamic code execution
- Do NOT store sensitive data in `localStorage` — use `chrome.storage`
- Do NOT use `XMLHttpRequest` — use `fetch()`
- Do NOT ignore `chrome.runtime.lastError`
